>Recent researches in Music Online,</subfield><subfield code=\"x\">2577-4573</subfield><subfield code=\"0\">(uri) http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/no2021011879</subfield><subfield code=\"0\">(uri) http://viaf.org/viaf/sourceID/LC|no2021011879</subfield></datafield><datafield tag=\"500\" ind1=\" \" ind2=\" \"><subfield code=\"a\">Vocal works for 3-4 voices; intabulations for lute, cittern, and keyboard.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag=\"500\" ind1=\" \" ind2=\" \"><subfield code=\"a\">Lute and cittern versions in tablature and staff notation.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag=\"546\" ind1=\" \" ind2=\" \"><subfield code=\"a\">Italian words, also printed as texts with English translations, pages xxxviii-lvi.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag=\"500\" ind1=\" \" ind2=\" \"><subfield code=\"a\">Includes introduction.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag=\"520\" ind1=\" \" ind2=\" \"><subfield code=\"a\">\"Lasso's canzoni villanesche are offered for the first time with their Neapolitan models and instrumental intabulations for lute, cittern, and keyboard. Although printed at widely separated times during his life (1555 and 1581), the canzoni reflect Lasso's youthful enthusiasm for Neapolitan song traditions and comic arts of deception. An extensive preface to the edition concerns the inception, transmission, and reception of these engaging songs and discusses principles of their arrangement for a variety of mixed ensembles.\" --</subfield><subfield code=\"c\">Provided by publisher.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag=\"588\" ind1=\" \" ind2=\" \"><subfield code=\"a\">Online resource (A-R Editions, viewed January 16, 2021).</subfield></datafield><datafield tag=\"504\" ind1=\" \" ind2=\" \"><subfield code=\"a\">Includes bibliographical references (pages xxix-xxxiii).</subfield></datafield><datafield tag=\"505\" ind1=\"0\" ind2=\" \"><subfield code=\"a\">Villanesche from Lasso's \"Opus I\" (1555): La cortesia voi donne predicate ; Madonna mia, pietà chiam'et aita ; 'No giorno t'haggio havere intra 'ste mane ; 'Sto core mio se fosse di diamante ; Tu sai, madonna mia, ch'io t'amo et voglio ; Tu, traditora, m'hai puost'a 'sto core -- Neapolitan Models for Lasso's Villanesche: La cortesia voi donne predicate, Vicenzo Fontana ; Madonna mia, pietà chiam'et aita, Vicenzo Fontana ; 'No giorno t'hagio havere intra 'ste mane, Vicenzo Fontana ; 'Sto core mio se fusse de diamante, Anon. ; Tu sai, madonna mia, ch'io t'amo e voglio, Vicenzo Fontana -- Villanelle from Lasso's \"Libro de villanelle\" (1581): Ad altre le voi dare 'ste passate ; Ecco la nimph' Ebrayca chiamata ; Io ti voria contar la pena mia ; O belle, fusa! chi ne vo' accatare? ; O occhi manza mia, cigli dorati ; Ogni giorno m'han ditt'a chi favelli ; Par ch'hai lasciato de non t'affacciare ; Saccio 'na cosa ch'è di legn'e tonda ; S'io fusse ciaul'et tu lo campanile ; S'io ti vedess'una sol volt'il giorno ; S'io ve dico ca sete la chiù bella ; Tutto lo dì mi dici, \"canta, canta\" -- Neapolitan Models for Lasso's Villanelle: Ad altre lo voi dare 'ste passate / Don Ioan Domenico del Giovane de Nola ; Ecco la nimph'Ebraica chiamata / Don Ioan Domenico del Giovane de Nola ; O belle, fusa! chi ne vo' accatare? / Don Ioan Domenico del Giovane de Nola ; O occhi manza mia, cigli dorati, Anon. ; Sacio 'na cosa ch'è di legno e tonda / Vicenzo Fontana -- Intabulations for Lute: La cortesia / [Orlando di Lasso/Sixt Kargel] ; Madonna mia pietà / [Orlando di Lasso/Sixt Kargel] ; Madonna mia pietà / [Orlando di Lasso/Emanuel Adriansen] ; Madonna mia pietà / [Orlando di Lasso/Emanuel Adriansen] ; Sto core mio / [Orlando di Lasso/Sixt Kargel] ; Tu sai madona / [Orlando di Lasso/Sixt Kargel] ; Tu traditore / [Orlando di Lasso/Sixt Kargel] -- Intabulations for Four-Course Cittern: La cortesia / [Orlando di Lasso/Anon.] ; Madona mia pietà / [Orlando di Lasso/Anon.] ; Madonna mia pietà / [Orlando di Lasso/Sixt Kargel] ; Sto core mio / [Orlando di Lasso/Anon.] ; Tu traditora / [Orlando di Lasso/Anon.] -- Intabulations for Six-Course Cittern: La cortesia / [Orlando di Lasso/Sixt Kargel] ; Madonna mia pietà / [Orlando di Lasso/Sixt Kargel] ; Tu sai ma donna / [Orlando di Lasso/Sixt Kargel] -- Intabulations for Keyboard: La cortesia / Orlande [de Lassus/Anon.] ; No giorno / Orlande de Lassus/[Anon.].</subfield></datafield><datafield tag=\"590\" ind1=\" \" ind2=\" \"><subfield code=\"a\">Available to current Emory faculty, students and staff.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag=\"598\" ind1=\" \" ind2=\" \"><subfield code=\"a\">NEW</subfield></datafield><datafield tag=\"650\" ind1=\" \" ind2=\"0\"><subfield code=\"a\">Villanelle (Part songs)</subfield><subfield code=\"z\">Italy</subfield><subfield code=\"y\">16th century</subfield><subfield code=\"v\">Scores.</subfield><subfield code=\"0\">(uri) http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh87002061</subfield></datafield><datafield tag=\"650\" ind1=\" \" ind2=\"0\"><subfield code=\"a\">Intabulations.</subfield><subfield code=\"0\">(uri) http://id.loc.gov/authorities/genreForms/gf2014027204</subfield><subfield code=\"0\">(uri) http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh89001222</subfield></datafield><datafield tag=\"655\" ind1=\" \" ind2=\"0\"><subfield code=\"a\">Electronic books.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag=\"655\" ind1=\" \" ind2=\"7\"><subfield code=\"a\">Scores.</subfield><subfield code=\"2\">lcgft</subfield><subfield code=\"0\">(uri) http://id.loc.gov/authorities/genreForms/gf2014027077</subfield></datafield><datafield tag=\"655\" ind1=\" \" ind2=\"7\"><subfield code=\"a\">Villanelle (Songs)</subfield><subfield code=\"2\">lcgft</subfield><subfield code=\"0\">(uri) http://id.loc.gov/authorities/genreForms/gf2014027189</subfield></datafield><datafield tag=\"655\" ind1=\" \" ind2=\"7\"><subfield code=\"a\">Intabulations.</subfield><subfield code=\"2\">lcgft</subfield><subfield code=\"0\">(uri) http://id.loc.gov/authorities/genreForms/gf2014027204</subfield><subfield code=\"0\">(uri) http: